data.enText: having the ability or qualities necessary for doing sth

data.chText: 靠撒谎渡过难关他挺有一套。
data.enText: He's quite capable of lying to get out of trouble.

data.chText: 谢谢，我完全有能力自己做。
data.enText: I'm perfectly capable of doing it myself, thank you.

data.chText: 你有能力做得比这更好。
data.enText: You are capable of better work than this.
having the ability to do things well

data.chText: 她是一位能力很强的教师。
我要把组织工作交给你这位能手。
data.enText: I'll leave the organization in your capable hands.

ex.chText: 她是一个能干的家庭主妇。
这个女婴能站起来走路了。
ex.enText: The baby girl is able to stand up and walk.

synonyms.bx: 指体力或智力方面有能力胜任的，作表语时常后接动词不定式，表示“能够…的”、“会…的”。

ex.chText: 我妈妈是个健壮、能干的女人。
ex.enText: My mother is a strong, capable woman.

ex.chText: 她已成为一名有本领的飞行员。
ex.enText: She has become a capable pilot.

ex.chText: 他将把球队交给你这位能手。
ex.enText: He'll leave the team in your capable hands.
He is capable of doing everything.

ex.chText: 这个大厅能容纳大约三百人。
ex.enText: The hall is capable of holding about three hundred people.

synonyms.bx: 指具有接受、适应等能力的，强调足以胜任某事；作表语时常后接介词 of，表示“能…的”，其主语可以是人或物。

example: the work isn't up to the standard I require

tr: (usually followed by `of') having capacity or ability
example: capable of walking on two feet

tr: (followed by `of') having the temperament or inclination for
example: no one believed her capable of murder

tr: have the skills and qualifications to do things well
example: children as young as 14 can be extremely capable and dependable
the time is fixed by the director and players and therefore subject to much variation

value.def: If a person or thing is capable of doing something, they have the ability to do it.

example.ex: He appeared hardly capable of conducting a coherent conversation...
example.tran: 他好像连话都说不清楚。

example.ex: The kitchen is capable of catering for several hundred people...
example.tran: 厨房能同时容纳数百人进餐。

example.ex: I had no hesitation in calling the police because I realised he was capable of murder.
example.tran: 我意识到他可能要杀人,所以就毫不犹豫地报了警。

value.def: Someone who is capable has the skill or qualities necessary to do a particular thing well, or is able to do most things well.

example.ex: Her husband was such a fine, capable man.

value.tran: 熟练的;胜任的;有能力的

example.ex: Happily it was all dealt with very capably by the police and security people.
example.tran: 幸好,警方和安保人员进行了非常妥善的处理。

value.boxu_tran: 注意, capable 和 able 都可用来表示能够做某事。able 表示具有必要知识或技能, 或者表示可能性: He wondered if he would be able to climb over the rail (他在想自己能不能翻越围栏)，They were able to use their profits for new investments (他们得以将利润用于新的投资)。注意, 如果用过去时, 则表示实际已经做了: We were able to reduce costs (我们得以降低成本)。capable表示具有所需的知识或技能, 或者表示可能做某事: The workers are perfectly capable of running the organization themselves (工人们完全有能力自己管理这个组织)，She was quite capable of falling asleep (她很容易睡着)。capable 后也可表示具有某种情感或做出某一行为: He's capable of loyalty (他能做到忠心耿耿)，Bowman could not believe him capable of murder (鲍曼不相信他会杀人)。capable of 还可以用于描述汽车或机器等的性能: The car was capable of 110 miles per hour (该车时速能达到110英里)。able 或 capable 用来形容人时表示“有能力的”、“能力强的”：He's certainly a capable gardener (他绝对是个能干的园丁)。
value.boxu_usage: Note that capable and able are both used to say that someone can do something. When you say that someone is able to do something, you mean that they can do it either because of their knowledge or skill, or because it is possible. He wondered if he would be able to climb over the rail... They were able to use their profits for new investments. Note that if you use a past tense, you are saying that someone has actually done something. We were able to reduce costs. When you say that someone is capable of doing something, you mean either that they have the knowledge and skill to do it, or that they are likely to do it. The workers are perfectly capable of running the organization themselves... She was quite capable of falling asleep. You can say that someone is capable of a particular feeling or action. He's capable of loyalty... Bowman could not believe him capable of murder. You can also use 'capable of' when talking about what something such as a car or machine can do. The car was capable of 110 miles per hour. If you describe someone as able or capable, you mean that they do things well. He's certainly a capable gardener.
